From: qinf-build <build@qinf.local>
Subject: [PATCH] qinf: add ggml_deltanet_post_state Metal backend (Phase 4)

PR 4.2.A — qinf downstream patch.

Adds the Metal backend for GGML_OP_DELTANET_POST_STATE: the fused kernel
itself (kernel_deltanet_post_state_f32 in ggml-metal.metal), the
dispatch case + ggml_metal_op_deltanet_post_state op function, the
supports_op gate, the pipeline lookup, and the kargs struct.

This is the GPU half of the op introduced by 0002. Constraints:
  - F32 dst + all srcs
  - src0/src1/src2 contiguous
  - ne00 (head_v_dim) % 32 == 0  (one simdgroup of reduction per row)

If supports_op returns false (e.g. quantized inputs slip in), the ggml
scheduler falls back to the CPU forward from 0002 — partial-Metal does
not break correctness.

Equivalence verified by tests/unit/test_deltanet_post_state.cpp on both
CPU and Metal backends, same tolerance band (1e-5 abs / 1e-4 rel,
matching the gated_delta_net upstream test).

Apply order: must be applied AFTER 0001 and 0002. apply-all.sh
enforces lexical order of patches/*.patch.

Files touched:
  ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal-impl.h     — kargs struct
  ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal-device.h   — pipeline-lookup decl
  ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal-device.cpp — pipeline-lookup impl
  ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal-device.m   — supports_op case
  ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal-ops.h      — op-fn decl
  ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal-ops.cpp    — dispatch case + op fn
  ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal.metal      — kernel_deltanet_post_state_f32

